rComments: This class was AMAZING!! she gives a TON of online reading, which you do NOT have to even do to participate in the discussions, nor will she normally be able to tell if you actually read. a couple EASY papers and projects. basically she loves everything you do and everything you say is "interesting!" she makes you feel like a genius.

Possibly the easiest class I have ever taken. Fun topics and projects: a couple response papers and power points. Silverman talks a lot and loves the word 'interesting'! Overall a very enjoyable class!
Easy peasy.  Adorable little lady who loves her cat. Some hate her, some love her... Just go along with her nuttiness and you'll be fine.

This was one of the easiest classes I've ever taken. All you need to do is attend lectures, which for some people is apparently too difficult. I found the lectures interesting and she was always willing to answer questions and she's obviously very knowlegable. I highly recommend her class IF you will commit to the lectures.
very simple class but try to make it to lecture and you will get an a for sure
Usually interesting, only grades are midterm and final. She thinks a lot of herself, but is knowledgeable about her field. Easy to skip some lectures and still be ok. Watch A LOT of movies.
Helaine was one of the best professors I had. She does interesting research and her classes are pretty fun. I mean, where else can you watch 'The Emperor's New Groove' for class credit?
Extremely bitter.  She demonstrates biases toward certain students.
